Mage Relm: Do you remember what happened before we fought
the dragon?
Mage Relm: It's when we all bumped our fists together...

Thief Nora: I remember! It's the one where we all exchanged
insults together, right?!
Mage Relm: Well, yes... but how about we do that?
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, that sounds nice, doesn't it?
Priestess Sophia: Then, let me start right away.

Priestess Sophia: I liked Clea-chan's courageous attitude of
going from recklessness, but you must never let your guard
down. Always prioritize your own life, okay?

Clea: I admire Relm-san for being serious about her dreams,
but please don't become so obsessed that you can only see
what's in front of you.

Mage Relm: I think Nora-san has changed a lot! But she still
lacks the confidence like mine!

Thief Nora: Sophia-san is a kind older sister and I love
her! But instead of drinking too much and throwing up,
please express your complaints more!

Clea: There were actually more compliments than insults,
weren't there?

Priestess Sophia: I see... I think mine was more like an
insult.

Mage Relm: This is our growth! Hehe, it means we're getting
closer to perfection!

Thief Nora: If that's the case, I want to say it to
everyone!
Mage Relm: In that case, I want to say it to everyone too!

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, it seems like we all feel the same
way.
Clea: Let's talk about that after everything is over.

Clea: Last time, we fought for ourselves, but this time,
it's for the people we've met on our journey...

Clea: Let's definitely defeat that monster, the dragon, for
the sake of someone living in the empire.
